{"id":"mai-7q8j","kind":"ticket","type":"task","title":"You are a HOSTILE test engineer. Your mission: write the most brutal, adversarial tests for the `pkg/git` package — the plumbing layer that everything else depends on.\n\n## Working Directory\n\nRead these files first:\n- `pkg/git/git.go` (1248 lines — 62 methods on GitRepo: notes read/write, diff, merge, refs, blobs, trees, commits)\n- `pkg/git/repo.go` (Repo interface — 370 lines)\n- `pkg/git/mock_repo.go` (mock implementation — 694 lines)\n- `pkg/git/types.go` (OID, Note, NotesRef, etc.)\n- `pkg/git/git_test.go` (ONLY 2 tests currently — pathetic)\n\n## Output\n\nCreate `pkg/git/git_adversarial_test.go` in the `git` package. These are REAL integration tests that create actual git repos in temp dirs.\n\n## Setup pattern\n\nEvery test creates a temp git repo:\n```go\nfunc setupGitRepo(t *testing.T) *GitRepo {\n    t.Helper()\n    dir := t.TempDir()\n    cmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"init\", dir)\n    cmd.Run()\n    // config user\n    exec.Command(\"git\", \"-C\", dir, \"config\", \"user.name\", \"Test\").Run()\n    exec.Command(\"git\", \"-C\", dir, \"config\", \"user.email\", \"test@test.com\").Run()\n    // initial commit\n    os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"README.md\"), []byte(\"# Test\"), 0644)\n    exec.Command(\"git\", \"-C\", dir, \"add\", \"-A\").Run()\n    exec.Command(\"git\", \"-C\", dir, \"commit\", \"-m\", \"init\").Run()\n    repo, _ := NewGitRepo(dir)\n    return repo\n}\n```\n\n## What to test — be VICIOUS\n\n### Notes operations (the foundation)\n1. AppendNote + GetNotes round-trip — write a note, read it back\n2. AppendNote multiple notes to same revision — all returned\n3. GetNotes on revision with no notes — empty slice, not nil/panic\n4. GetAllNotes across multiple revisions\n5. ListNotedRevisions — correct set\n6. AppendNote with empty content\n7. AppendNote with huge content (100KB+)\n8. AppendNote with special characters, newlines, unicode, JSON\n9. Notes on commits that get amended — do notes survive?\n\n### Ref operations\n10. HasRef for existing/non-existing refs\n11. SetRef + verify with GetCommitHash\n12. VerifyGitRef with valid/invalid refs\n13. VerifyCommit with valid/invalid OIDs\n14. GetHeadRef on branch vs detached HEAD\n15. ResolveRefCommit on tags, branches, SHAs\n\n### Diff/Merge/Ancestry\n16. Diff between two commits with changes — verify output\n17. Diff with --stat flag\n18. Diff between identical commits — empty string\n19. MergeBase between diverged branches\n20. MergeBase between linear commits\n21. IsAncestor: true case, false case, same commit\n22. IsAncestor with non-existent ref — error, not panic\n23. MergeRef fast-forward\n24. MergeRef no-ff with message\n25. MergeRef with conflict — error handling\n\n### Blob/Tree/Commit operations\n26. StoreBlob + readBlob round-trip\n27. StoreBlob with empty string\n28. StoreBlob with binary-ish content\n29. StoreTree with nested entries\n30. ReadTree — verify structure\n31. CreateCommit + verify GetCommitMessage\n32. CreateCommitWithTree\n\n### Branch/Commit listing\n33. ListCommits — correct order\n34. ListCommitsBetween — correct range\n35. ListCommitsBetween with same from/to — empty\n36. Show file at specific commit\n37. Show non-existent file — error\n\n### Edge cases that cause silent corruption\n38. Concurrent AppendNote to same ref from goroutines\n39. GetNotes after notes ref is force-deleted\n40. NewGitRepo on non-git directory — error\n41. NewGitRepo on non-existent path — error\n42. Operations on repo after .git directory is corrupted\n\n### Notes merge (critical for sync)\n43. MergeNotes with non-overlapping notes — union\n44. MergeNotes with duplicate notes — dedup\n45. PullNotes from remote\n\n## Build and run\n\n```bash\nnix-shell -p go --run 'go test ./pkg/git/ -count=1 -timeout 180s -v'\n```\n\nAlso verify ALL existing tests still pass:\n```bash\nnix-shell -p go --run 'go test ./... -count=1 -timeout 180s'\n```\n\n## Rules\n- Every test must PASS. If you find actual bugs, write the test to document current behavior with `// BUG:` comment.\n- REAL git repos only — no mocks. This is an integration test file.\n- Set `GIT_AUTHOR_NAME`, `GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL`, `GIT_COMMITTER_NAME`, `GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL` env vars in your setup or via git config.\n- Use `t.Run()` subtests.\n- Error messages must show got/want.\n- Commit when all tests pass.","assignee":"adversarial-git-2","tags":["team"],"body":"You are a HOSTILE test engineer. Your mission: write the most brutal, adversarial tests for the `pkg/git` package — the plumbing layer that everything else depends on.\n\n## Working Directory\n\nRead these files first:\n- `pkg/git/git.go` (1248 lines — 62 methods on GitRepo: notes read/write, diff, merge, refs, blobs, trees, commits)\n- `pkg/git/repo.go` (Repo interface — 370 lines)\n- `pkg/git/mock_repo.go` (mock implementation — 694 lines)\n- `pkg/git/types.go` (OID, Note, NotesRef, etc.)\n- `pkg/git/git_test.go` (ONLY 2 tests currently — pathetic)\n\n## Output\n\nCreate `pkg/git/git_adversarial_test.go` in the `git` package. These are REAL integration tests that create actual git repos in temp dirs.\n\n## Setup pattern\n\nEvery test creates a temp git repo:\n```go\nfunc setupGitRepo(t *testing.T) *GitRepo {\n    t.Helper()\n    dir := t.TempDir()\n    cmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"init\", dir)\n    cmd.Run()\n    // config user\n    exec.Command(\"git\", \"-C\", dir, \"config\", \"user.name\", \"Test\").Run()\n    exec.Command(\"git\", \"-C\", dir, \"config\", \"user.email\", \"test@test.com\").Run()\n    // initial commit\n    os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"README.md\"), []byte(\"# Test\"), 0644)\n    exec.Command(\"git\", \"-C\", dir, \"add\", \"-A\").Run()\n    exec.Command(\"git\", \"-C\", dir, \"commit\", \"-m\", \"init\").Run()\n    repo, _ := NewGitRepo(dir)\n    return repo\n}\n```\n\n## What to test — be VICIOUS\n\n### Notes operations (the foundation)\n1. AppendNote + GetNotes round-trip — write a note, read it back\n2. Append